### 8.3 Row-Level Security (sample)
```sql
-- Enable RLS on attendance_record table
ALTER TABLE att_attendance_record ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Policy: users can only see their tenant's data
CREATE POLICY tenant_isolation_policy ON att_attendance_record
    FOR ALL
    USING (tenant_id = current_setting('app.tenant_id')::uuid);

-- Policy: teachers can only mark attendance for their own classes
CREATE POLICY teacher_class_policy ON att_attendance_record
    FOR INSERT
    WITH CHECK (
        teacher_id = current_setting('app.user_id')::uuid
        AND EXISTS (
            SELECT 1 FROM class_assignments ca
            WHERE ca.teacher_id = current_setting('app.user_id')::uuid
            AND ca.class_id = (SELECT class_id FROM students WHERE id = student_id)
        )
    );
```

### 8.4 Indexes We Need
- `idx_attendance_student_date` ON `att_attendance_record(tenant_id, student_id, attendance_date)` — supports student history queries
- `idx_attendance_class_period` ON `att_attendance_record(tenant_id, campus_id, attendance_date, period_number)` — supports class roster queries
- `idx_biometric_device_time` ON `att_biometric_event(tenant_id, device_id, scan_timestamp)` — supports device sync queries
- `idx_anomaly_status` ON `att_anomaly(tenant_id, campus_id, status, severity)` — supports anomaly dashboard queries
- `idx_attendance_notification` ON `att_attendance_record(tenant_id, absent_notif_sent, attendance_date)` WHERE `status = 'absent'` — supports notification retry queries

