## 14. Security, Audit and Data Safety

### 14.1 What is Protected and How
| What | How |
|------|-----|
| **Student PII** | AES-256 encryption at rest (Aadhaar, medical data) |
| **Biometric Data** | Never stored — only hash templates in device |
| **Parent Contacts** | DPDP consent flags enforced (`whatsapp_consent`, `sms_consent`) |
| **Teacher Credentials** | bcrypt with work factor ≥12, MFA for admin roles |
| **Device Secrets** | AWS Secrets Manager, rotated every 90 days |
| **JWT Tokens** | RS256 signed, 8-hour TTL, refresh token rotation |
| **Audit Trail** | Immutable log — who changed what, when, before/after values |
| **RLS Policies** | Enforced at DB level — tenant isolation guaranteed |

